When an edge becomes many times heavier than its adjacent edges,
a smaller-cut solution exists. However, MLPart may not find it
because clustering and uncoarsening restrict the refinement path.
For a moderately heavier weight, what matters is how many adjacent edges
must become cut to allow this edge to be uncut.
